title: Landon Young received his U.S. Army All-American jersey today
text:
Article written by Drew Franklin I can recite every line from Forrest Gump, blindfolded. Follow me on Twitter: @DrewFranklinKSR 7 responses to “Landon Young received his U.S. Army All-American jersey today” ClutchCargo October 26, 2015 at 4:03 pm | Permalink | Reply 
That’s great! Can’t wait to see these guys in blue next year and beyond. Pete October 26, 2015 at 4:25 pm | Permalink | Reply 
Perfect 2 Offensive Linemen and a Linebacker. Get here quick! john wall October 26, 2015 at 4:32 pm | Permalink | Reply 
Landon Young just seems like a good ole boy from the country ClutchCargo October 26, 2015 at 4:36 pm | Permalink 
That’s exactly what he is. It’s also a factor in wanting to stay in-state vs. going to one of the out of state powerhouse programs. BenHur October 26, 2015 at 4:34 pm | Permalink | Reply 
Clydesdales BluKudzu October 26, 2015 at 4:34 pm | Permalink | Reply 
The commonwealth is very proud of you, and thank you for your commitment to UK. We need your best, for us to be our best! Congratulations on your acheivemnt! October 26, 2015 at 4:41 pm | Permalink | Reply 
I love how these in-state boys are there supporting each other. Post Comment - New and Improved (not really, it just works now)
